<div><h3>FIN 5401 - Investments </h3>  <hr>This course provides an introduction to the financial market, investment theory, and security valuation. The topics covered include equity and bond pricing, portfolio analysis, capital asset pricing model, behavioral finance, option pricing, and ethics in investment management. Emerging topics such as ESG (Environmental, Social and Governance) investing, FinTech, and Cryptocurrency, will be discussed. The lectures and examinations will focus both on conceptual and quantitative foundations.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> No prerequisites for MSF students. Prerequisite for other students is <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=97483" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=97483&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=97483&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt573" target="_blank">FIN 4200</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered Annually<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt573"></div></div>		</td>
